## Conjecture (CPRR)
Three independent hypotheses bundled because they all live in ollama.scm:

1. After ollama rm, sage should pick the smallest chat-capable
   substitute and warn the user, not crash. \"Smallest\" is the right
   default because the user just freed disk and probably wants
   tighter feedback loops.

2. The Ollama streaming protocol places tool_calls in the FIRST
   chunk (done:false), not the last. Any client that only inspects
   the done chunk will silently lose tool calls.

3. sage's JSON parser returns arrays as Scheme lists; downstream
   code that hard-codes vector? for tool_calls is broken regardless
   of which API path it's on.

