## Refutation / known limits
- The fallback heuristic doesn't know about reasoning models like
  qwen3:0.6b. On this box it picks qwen3:0.6b as smallest chat-capable
  but qwen3 emits long <think> chains, bloating token counters.
  Filed in RELEASE-0.6.0.org as a known characteristic.
- llama3.2 STILL sometimes text-formats tool calls instead of using
  the native tool_calls field. The fix here only catches the case
  where the model DOES use the native field. The fallback parser
  for ```tool fenced blocks doesn't catch raw inline JSON either.
  Documented as the \">= 3B\" model selection rationale in
  RELEASE-0.6.0.org.
- 404 detection assumes Ollama; cloud providers may use different
  status codes / error shapes.
- select-fallback-model picks by size only. A smarter heuristic
  could prefer known tool-capable families (qwen2.5, llama3.x) over
  reasoning models (qwen3) but we don't expose that info from
  /api/tags.

